Definition: the speed at which light travels in a vacuum
Example: the constancy and universality of the speed of light is recognized by defining it to be exactly 299,792,458 meters per second
Synonyms: light_speed, c, speed, noun, quantity, constant, the, at, which, light, travels, in, a, vacuum, constancy, and, universality, of, is, recognized, by, defining, it, to, be, exactly, meters, per, second
Category: noun.time
